00:05:00.090 --> 00:05:04.670
Now I would like to introduce
today's speaker, Dr. Paul Dolinsky.

00:05:04.670 --> 00:05:07.900
Dr. Paul Dolinsky has
long been associated

00:05:07.900 --> 00:05:12.460
with historic preservation
in general and architecture

00:05:12.460 --> 00:05:16.950
and in landscape architecture
documentation in particular.

00:05:16.950 --> 00:05:21.310 position:56%
Professionally trained in
architecture, landscape architecture

00:05:21.310 --> 00:05:25.650
and architectural history, he
was uniquely qualified to work

00:05:25.650 --> 00:05:29.190
with the Historic American
Building Survey, HABS,

00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:31.630
of the National Park Service.

00:05:31.630 --> 00:05:37.170
Dr. Dolinsky began to
work with HABS in 1979

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:39.360
as an architectural
technician working

00:05:39.360 --> 00:05:42.570
with teams measuring
historic structures

00:05:42.570 --> 00:05:46.100 position:56%
and producing ink on miter drawings.

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:49.270
He eventually became
a project supervisor

00:05:49.270 --> 00:05:54.000
and a national chief
of program in 1993.

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:58.330
During tenure as chief,
he instituted many changes

00:05:58.330 --> 00:06:02.810
to the program, such as
computer-aided drafting,

00:06:02.810 --> 00:06:07.780
[inaudible] distance-measuring
devices, photogrammetry

00:06:07.780 --> 00:06:10.680
and additional laser
measuring as well

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:15.310
as significantly expanding the
historic research components.

00:06:15.310 --> 00:06:20.480 position:56%
During the 1980s, there was a
strong interest in the unique nature

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:23.120
of historic landscape architecture

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:26.270
with the cultural landscape
movement.

00:06:26.270 --> 00:06:32.650
Dr. Dolinsky was instrumental in
developing a series of projects

00:06:32.650 --> 00:06:35.610
that ultimately resulted
in the creation

00:06:35.610 --> 00:06:40.840
of the Historic American
Landscape Survey, HALS, in 2000,

00:06:40.840 --> 00:06:43.870
with the American Society
of Landscape Architects,

00:06:43.870 --> 00:06:48.030
National Park Service and
the Library of Congress.

00:06:48.030 --> 00:06:51.860
This rapidly-expanding program
has been extremely effective

00:06:51.860 --> 00:06:58.490
in the last 16 years, now
having representation in 49

00:06:58.490 --> 00:07:01.040
of the 50 states as well

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:04.950
as significant landscape
documentation American soil abroad.

00:07:04.950 --> 00:07:11.520
Dr. Paul Dolinsky has been serving
and contributing as chief of HALS

00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:13.920
since it was established.

