of that beautiful ironwork.

00:11:55.140 --> 00:12:00.480
The success of the four-month
temporary relief was obvious.

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:03.790 position:56%
It needed to be done on a
long-term basis and it was validated

00:12:03.790 --> 00:12:06.390
by a permanent plan for
approval and disposition

00:12:06.390 --> 00:12:10.700
of all future graphic records of
historic American architecture.

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:15.950
That is Gustav Rohrich standing in
front of his sod house in Nebraska.

00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:18.710
There are very few sod
houses, I think, if any left,

00:12:18.710 --> 00:12:22.500
and on the left side is --

00:12:22.500 --> 00:12:26.770
right, left, is the measured
drawing not only of the house

00:12:26.770 --> 00:12:29.450
but of the way the sod is
actually packed together

00:12:29.450 --> 00:12:31.630 position:56%
