00:16:56.300 --> 00:17:01.690
but the important message here
is these drawings, histories

00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:04.850
and photographs that were
produced ultimately informed sort

00:17:04.850 --> 00:17:07.300
of the burgeoning cultural
landscape movement.

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:10.350
You needed this information,
you needed these types

00:17:10.350 --> 00:17:14.060 position:56%
of measured drawings, the
supporting research and photographs,

00:17:14.060 --> 00:17:17.520
to inform the analysis and
treatment recommendations

00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:19.090 position:56%
for the preservation of these sites.

00:17:19.090 --> 00:17:23.640
And here you'll see the Meridian
Hill drawings, and that is a copy

00:17:23.640 --> 00:17:26.610
of the cultural landscape report
which is currently being used

00:17:26.610 --> 00:17:29.840
in the restoration of Meridian
Hill Park, so in essence,

00:17:29.840 --> 00:17:32.670
we were building the case of
the establishment of HALS.

00:17:32.670 --> 00:17:35.270
All this ultimately informed
the establishment of HALS

00:17:35.270 --> 00:17:36.970
and the landscape survey

00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:41.250
because landscape architecture
is indeed unique.

00:17:41.250 --> 00:17:45.720
So that's a lot of background
covered very quickly,

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:50.850
actually about 50 years of HABS and
another 25 years of HALS to get us

00:17:50.850 --> 00:17:53.880
up to the present, and like I said,
we only have about a half-hour

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:56.850
or so here, so hopefully this
will intrigue you enough.

00:17:56.850 --> 00:18:00.030 position:56%
If you just search it on any engine,
